Bennerd James CRAIG v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 6102. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. June 15, 1959. James W. Wilson, Denver, Colo., for appellant. Paul W. Cress, U. S. Atty., and George Camp, Asst. U. S. Atty., Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellee.

Before MURRAH, PICKETT and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on ground that the notice of appeal was filed out of time.
